The attempted murder and malicious damage to property trial of controversial farm manager Mark Scott-Crossely has been set to resume in the Naphuno magistrate’s court in Lenyenye outside Tzaneen in Limpopo on Monday. He allegedly knocked down a farm worker, Silence Mabunda and broke his cell phone in a suspected racial altercation in Hoedspruit in 2016. Scott- Crossely has pleaded not guilty. His trial started last year December. He was arrested in 2017 after evading trial for a month. He is not new in controversy, in 2005, the Phalaborwa Circuit court found him guilty of throwing his employee Nelson Chisane into a lion enclosure. However, the Supreme court of Appeal  set aside his murder conviction. It then gave him five years imprisonment. He was released on parole in August 2008. Watch related videos:    